# Free & Open Grant Proposal Technical Template
## Project name
The name of the project is: MidoriSale

## Project overview

### General
Our project is for having token sale on blockchain.
Sellers can start token sale.
Earlier holders buy, and Larger amount holders buy, they get more midori tokens.  
Sellers pay fee on having token sale, midori token holders get a part of that fee according to amount of the tokens.
Concordium fits this project because it has KYC protcol, it only can prevent money laundering and financing of terrorism and fraud.

### Description 
Final project: Full-decentralized and automated bond-issue application on concordium blockchain
Steps to reach our goal:
1. Develop and release the beta-version product
2. Find organizations which want to issue bonds
3. Get feedback from these organizations
4. Develop and release the official version product.
Current problems/issues:
1. What data should we get from blockchain?
2. How we exclude fraudlent address/transactions in order to acheive AML/CFT?
How Concordium help us: We can exclude suspicious transactions thanks to Concordium KYC system

### Submission
Please submit the following (if and when relevant): 
* Mockups of any UI components
* Tech specifications
* Tech stack overview
* Documentation of the core compononets, protocols, architecture etc. to be deployed
* PoC/MVP 
